Page 2: Transmission Delay & Bandwidth
Transmission Delay:
The time taken to place the complete data packet onto the transmission medium.
It is the time spent by the sender placing the data that is ready to be transferred.
Bandwidth:
It is the maximum amount of data capacity that can be transmitted through a network per second.
It represents how much data can be transmitted in the real world in one second.
Analogy: Think of it as the size of a channel; it determines how much data is transferred per second.

